they
proved
to
be
French
compositions,
written
in
a
hand
peculiar
but
compact,
and
exquisitely
clean
and
clear.
The
writing
was
recognizable.
She
scarcely
needed
the
further
evidence
of
the
name
signed
at
the
close
of
each
theme
to
tell
her
whose
