room.
She
made
lesson
time
charming.
She
learned
fast
you
could
hardly
tell
when
or
how.
French
was
nothing
to
her.
She
spoke
it
quick,
quick
as
quick
as
Mr.
Moore
himself."
"Was
she
obedient?
Did
she
give
trouble?"
"She
gave
plenty
of
trouble,
in
a
way.
She
was
giddy,
but
I
liked
her.
I'm
desperately
fond
